100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 30, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing the ongoing tensions in the Ruhr region as France continued its occupation of the industrial area in Germany. Meanwhile, in the United States, the trial of the infamous Scopes "Monkey" case drew national attention, as debates over evolution versus creationism intensified. Additionally, the British Parliament debated the future of the British Empire, with discussions focusing on India’s potential self-governance.
